LMS Platform — Project Summary
What it is
A static, bundler-free SPA hosted on GitHub Pages. No server, no build step. Pure ES modules loaded directly in the browser. Firebase (Auth + Firestore) provides the only backend. All lesson content lives in standalone HTML files that work without the shell.

File structure
docs/
├── index.html                  ← SPA shell (fields landing + module/lesson UI)
└── lms/
    ├── core/
    │   ├── app.js              ← Main controller: state, routing, rendering, sync
    │   ├── registry.js         ← Single source of truth: modules, fields, config
    │   ├── auth.js             ← Firebase Auth wrapper (Google + email)
    │   ├── db.js               ← Firestore: profiles, progress, access, userIndex
    │   ├── access.js           ← Module visibility logic per user/platform mode
    │   ├── admin.js            ← Admin panel controller (standalone, never in app.js)
    │   ├── i18n.js             ← t(), loadLanguage(), applyTranslations()
    │   ├── firebase-config.js  ← Firebase project credentials
    │   └── styles.css          ← All shell styles
    ├── admin/
    │   └── index.html          ← Admin panel page (separate, requires admin role)
    ├── i18n/
    │   └── ar.js               ← Arabic translation overrides
    └── modules/{id}/lessons/   ← Standalone lesson HTML files (no shell dependency)

Current features (all implemented)
Phase 0 — Fields hierarchy

A full-page card grid is the first screen. Each card represents a field (e.g. "Backend Development") grouping multiple modules. Clicking a card enters the module/lesson shell scoped to that field. A back button returns to the landing. If no fields are configured, the shell loads directly — backward-compat mode.
Phase 1 — Generic platform

document.title, the brand heading, and the welcome panel all read from LMS_CONFIG at runtime. No hardcoded content in shell files.
Phase 2 — Multilingual (EN + AR)

English is the source of truth in-file; Arabic overrides live in ar.js. loadLanguage() fetches the override file, applyTranslations() patches data-i18n elements, and t(key, fallback) handles JS-rendered strings. Switching language persists to localStorage and flips RTL/LTR on <html>. The language switcher is in the sidebar.
Phase 3 — Authentication

Google Sign-In popup and email/password sign-up + sign-in. Auth state persists across page refresh (Firebase-native). Signed-in users see their avatar, display name, and tier badge in the sidebar. Errors surface inline below the form.
Phase 4 — Cross-device progress sync

Lesson HTML files write progress to localStorage only. app.js polls every 3 seconds and syncs to Firestore. On sign-in, Firestore progress is merged into localStorage (Firestore wins on conflict). Reset clears both stores. Anonymous mode works entirely via localStorage.
Phase 6 — Access control + admin panel

Two modes in registry.js: 'open' (all users see all modules by default) and 'controlled' (users see nothing until granted). Per-user access is stored in users/{uid}/access/modules as { moduleId: true|false }. Missing key falls through to the platform default. The admin panel at /lms/admin/ lists all accounts from the userIndex collection, with module toggles grouped by field and bulk "Grant field / Revoke field" actions. The admin link only appears in the sidebar for users with role: 'admin'.

What's NOT implemented
Phase 5 — Personalised lessons (designed but not built): AI-generated lesson content gated behind auth/pro tier, stored in Firestore, loaded via Blob URL into the iframe. The registry contract supports requiresAuth, requiresPro, and isPersonalised lesson flags but none of the current lessons use them.
Pro/payment tier: tier: 'free' | 'pro' exists in the Firestore profile and is displayed as a badge, but there is no payment integration and no pro-gated content yet.

Firestore data model
users/{uid}
  displayName, email, tier, lang, createdAt, lastSeen, role?

users/{uid}/progress/{storageKey}
  { checkboxKey: true|false, ... }

users/{uid}/access/modules
  { moduleId: true|false, ... }   ← missing key = platform default

userIndex/{uid}
  displayName, email, photoURL    ← admin-readable index of all accounts